The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, August 03, 2003 				 ISI agent held in Sikkim
 PROBIR PRAMANIK AND PEMA LEYDA SHANDERPA																								Siliguri/Gangtok, Aug. 2: The Sikkim Crime Branch this evening arrested an ISI agent snooping around the armys Black Cat cantonment at Deorali on the outskirts of Gangtok.																								Sikkim crime branch sleuths picked up 40-year-old Dilip Kumar Roy, a resident of Dhaka, around 5.30 pm in front of the Deorali Black Cat cantonment gate, said deputy inspector-general of police (range) S.D. Negi.																								Central and state intelligence agencies in Sikkim and Bengal termed Roys arrest as one of the biggest ISI catches in recent times.																								We have seized several incrementing documents from Roy. During interrogation, Roy admitted that he was working as an ISI agent. Roy claimed that he had entered India legally through Calcutta in the first week of April, Negi said. 
